# Quality Gates

A task is not complete until relevant gates pass:

- Before adding a test, check existing unit/integration/E2E/SQL tests for the
  same behavior. Extend the existing test when that is clearer; do not create
  duplicate test files, duplicate fixtures, duplicate mock accounts, or duplicate
  seed data for the same scenario.
- TypeScript strict checks.
- Lint and formatting checks.
- Unit tests for domain logic.
- E2E/smoke tests for critical flows. "Critical" includes every user-facing
  auth, wallet, reward, spot/futures, staking, casino, deposit, withdrawal,
  admin, permission, PWA, i18n mode, and mobile-shell flow.
- Money-affecting E2E must run against the local Supabase stack and assert DB
  invariants, not only visible text: wallet/system-account conservation per
  currency, hash-chain integrity when applicable, idempotency on duplicate
  submissions, and no test residue.
- Security/Admin E2E must include positive and negative authorization plus audit
  evidence. A hidden button is not enough; the server-trusted RPC/RLS path must
  reject unauthorized users.
- Casino E2E must include provably-fair verification: seed hash shown before the
  bet, revealed seed after settlement, client recomputation matching the stored
  outcome, and ledger conservation.
- Full Phase E2E is mandatory before any Phase is closed or launch-readiness is
  claimed. E2E failure blocks completion even when unit, SQL, lint, typecheck,
  and build pass.
- SQL migrations apply cleanly on a local Supabase (`supabase db reset`); apply-time errors are not caught by TS checks.
- SQL integration tests pass for money/settlement/liquidation/circuit-breaker RPCs, exercising the changed branch and asserting conservation + hash-chain integrity.
- Env and i18n coverage checks.
- Security review for Supabase/RLS/RPC or admin changes.
- Test residue cleanup.

Run these gates yourself, automatically, without asking (Docker/local stack
included — see `70-autonomy-and-delivery`). Additionally:

- No dev/test/"test mode" UI may ship; dev-only tooling is gated behind
  `import.meta.env.DEV`. Production builds must be clean and launch-ready.
- After each completed task, append an implementation + error/fix entry to the
  Build Log in `docs/PHONARA_V2_MASTER_PLAN.md`.
